tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits, including renal function, electrolytes, and lipid profile. Hemoglobin A1c is at the upper end of normal, suggesting good but borderline glycemic control. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected; recommend continued monitoring, especially of glucose metabolism.
